<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-09-23T10:08:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-09-23T10:08:00-05:00" n="1064" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1064">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">411.919/9–1853: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Embassy in
                                        India</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d1064fn1">This
                                    telegram was drafted by <persName corresp="#p_FJR1">Fluker</persName> of <gloss target="#t_SOA1">SOA</gloss>
                                    and was signed by <persName corresp="#p_KDD1">Kennedy</persName>.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-09-23T11:08:00-04:00">September 23, 1953—11:08
                                        a.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>332. <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 512.<note n="2" xml:id="d1064fn2"><ref target="#d1063"><hi rend="italic">Supra</hi></ref>.</note> Fear here that suggested
                                change in referenced third sentence liable to misinterpretation as
                                referring only to specific commodities you have discussed with
                                    <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> Suggest alternative
                                language: (1) In <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 512
                                substitute language in quotes insert phrase “including those” after
                                “commodities” and before clause beginning “which” or (2) In
                                referenced third sentence <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss>
                                    253,<note n="3" xml:id="d1064fn3">Dated Sept. 3, <ref target="#pg_1717">p. 1717</ref>.</note> substitute
                                “strategic” in lieu of “Battle Act.” Either amendment acceptable
                                here; if unacceptable <gloss target="#t_GOI1">GOI</gloss> Department
                                will attempt work out additional language to indicate that statement
                                involves the broad range of strategic commodities.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>